---
import Base from "@/layouts/Base.astro";
import { generatePaths } from "@/lib/utils/i18nUtils";

export function getStaticPaths() {
  return generatePaths();
}

const seo = {
  title: "Terms of Use",
  meta_title: "Terms of Use — NETLINKS Inc.",
  description:
    "NETLINKS Inc. Terms of Use. Read the terms governing your use of our website and services.",
};
---

<Base {...seo}>
  <section class="py-16">
    <div class="container max-w-4xl">
      <h1 class="text-dark mb-4 text-4xl font-bold">Terms of Use</h1>
      <p class="mb-12 text-sm text-gray-500">Last Updated: March 8, 2026</p>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none space-y-8 text-gray-700">
        <p>
          Welcome to the website of NETLINKS Inc. ("NETLINKS," "we," "us," or
          "our"), a technology company headquartered in Virginia, United States.
          By accessing or using our website at
          <a
            href="https://www.netlinks.net"
            class="text-primary hover:underline">
            www.netlinks.net
          </a>
          (the "Site"), you agree to be bound by these Terms of Use ("Terms"). If
          you do not agree to these Terms, please do not use the Site.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-dark text-2xl font-semibold">1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
        <p>
          By accessing, browsing, or using this Site, you acknowledge that you
          have read, understood, and agree to be bound by these Terms and our
          <a
            href="/company/privacy-policy/"
            class="text-primary hover:underline">
            Privacy Policy
          </a>, which is incorporated herein by reference. We reserve the right
          to modify these Terms at any time, and such modifications will be
          effective immediately upon posting on this Site.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-dark text-2xl font-semibold">2. Use of the Site</h2>
        <p>
          You agree to use the Site only for lawful purposes and in accordance
          with these Terms. You agree not to:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc space-y-1 pl-6">
          <li>
            Use the Site in any way that violates applicable federal, state,
            local, or international laws or regulations
          </li>
          <li>
            Impersonate or attempt to impersonate NETLINKS, a NETLINKS employee,
            or any other person or entity
          </li>
          <li>
            Engage in any conduct that restricts or inhibits anyone's use or
            enjoyment of the Site
          </li>
          <li>
            Introduce any viruses, worms, or other malicious code to the Site
          </li>
          <li>
            Attempt to gain unauthorized access to any portion of the Site,
            server, or systems connected to the Site
          </li>
          <li>
            Use any automated means (bots, scrapers, spiders) to access the Site
            for any purpose without our prior written consent
          </li>
          <li>
            Collect or harvest personal information of other users without their
            consent
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-dark text-2xl font-semibold">
          3. Intellectual Property Rights
        </h2>
        <p>
          The Site and its entire contents, features, and functionality —
          including but not limited to all text, graphics, logos, images, icons,
          audio clips, digital downloads, data compilations, software, and the
          design, selection, and arrangement thereof — are owned by NETLINKS
          Inc., its licensors, or other providers of such material and are
          protected by United States and international copyright, trademark,
          patent, trade secret, and other intellectual property or proprietary
          rights laws.
        </p>
        <p>
          The NETLINKS name, logo, and all related names, logos, product and
          service names, designs, and slogans are trademarks of NETLINKS Inc.
          You must not use such marks without our prior written permission.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-dark text-2xl font-semibold">
          4. Services Description
        </h2>
        <p>
          NETLINKS provides enterprise technology solutions, including but not
          limited to Odoo ERP implementation, customization, integration, and
          migration services; AI consulting and automation; custom software
          development; and web and mobile application development. Descriptions
          of services on the Site are for informational purposes only and do not
          constitute a binding offer or contract.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-dark text-2xl font-semibold">
          5. Contact Form Submissions
        </h2>
        <p>
          When you submit information through our contact forms, you consent to
          the processing of your personal data as described in our <a
            href="/company/privacy-policy/"
            class="text-primary hover:underline">
            Privacy Policy
          </a>. You represent that all information you provide is accurate and
          complete. Form submissions create leads in our CRM system for the
          purpose of responding to your inquiry and do not constitute a
          contractual agreement for services.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-dark text-2xl font-semibold">
          6. Third-Party Content and Links
        </h2>
        <p>
          The Site may contain links to third-party websites, resources, or
          services that are not owned or controlled by NETLINKS. We have no
          control over the content, privacy policies, or practices of any
          third-party websites. We do not endorse or assume any responsibility
          for any third-party sites, information, materials, products, or
          services.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-dark text-2xl font-semibold">
          7. Disclaimer of Warranties
        </h2>
        <p>
          THE SITE AND ALL INFORMATION, CONTENT, MATERIALS, AND SERVICES
          PROVIDED ON OR THROUGH THE SITE ARE PROVIDED "AS IS" AND "AS
          AVAILABLE" WITHOUT ANY WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND, EITHER EXPRESS OR
          IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO THE IMPLIED WARRANTIES OF
          MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, TITLE, AND
          NON-INFRINGEMENT.
        </p>
        <p>
          NETLINKS does not warrant that the Site will be uninterrupted,
          error-free, secure, or free of viruses or other harmful components.
          NETLINKS does not warrant or make any representations regarding the
          use or the results of the use of the content on the Site in terms of
          accuracy, reliability, or otherwise.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-dark text-2xl font-semibold">
          8. Limitation of Liability
        </h2>
        <p>
          TO THE FULLEST EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, NETLINKS INC., ITS OFFICERS,
          DIRECTORS, EMPLOYEES, AGENTS, AND AFFILIATES SHALL NOT BE LIABLE FOR
          ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES,
          INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO LOSS OF PROFITS, DATA, USE, GOODWILL, OR
          OTHER INTANGIBLE LOSSES, ARISING OUT OF OR RELATED TO YOUR USE OR
          INABILITY TO USE THE SITE OR ANY SERVICES PROVIDED THROUGH THE SITE,
          WHETHER BASED ON WARRANTY, CONTRACT, TORT (INCLUDING NEGLIGENCE),
          STATUTE, OR ANY OTHER LEGAL THEORY.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-dark text-2xl font-semibold">9. Indemnification</h2>
        <p>
          You agree to indemnify, defend, and hold harmless NETLINKS Inc. and
          its officers, directors, employees, agents, licensors, and affiliates
          from and against any claims, liabilities, damages, losses, costs, or
          expenses (including reasonable attorneys' fees) arising out of or in
          any way connected with your access to or use of the Site, your
          violation of these Terms, or your violation of any rights of another
          party.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-dark text-2xl font-semibold">
          10. Governing Law and Jurisdiction
        </h2>
        <p>
          These Terms shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the
          laws of the Commonwealth of Virginia, United States, without regard to
          its conflict of law provisions. You agree to submit to the exclusive
          jurisdiction of the state and federal courts located in the
          Commonwealth of Virginia for the resolution of any disputes arising
          out of or relating to these Terms or the Site.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-dark text-2xl font-semibold">11. Severability</h2>
        <p>
          If any provision of these Terms is held to be invalid, illegal, or
          unenforceable, the remaining provisions shall continue in full force
          and effect, and the invalid provision shall be modified to the minimum
          extent necessary to make it valid and enforceable.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-dark text-2xl font-semibold">12. Entire Agreement</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms, together with the Privacy Policy, constitute the entire
          agreement between you and NETLINKS Inc. regarding your use of the Site
          and supersede all prior and contemporaneous understandings,
          agreements, representations, and warranties, both written and oral.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-dark text-2xl font-semibold">13. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>If you have any questions about these Terms, please contact us:</p>
        <div class="rounded-lg bg-gray-50 p-6">
          <p class="text-dark font-semibold">NETLINKS Inc.</p>
          <p>Virginia, United States</p>
          <p>
            Email: <a
              href="mailto:info@netlinks.net"
              class="text-primary hover:underline">
              info@netlinks.net
            </a>
          </p>
          <p>
            Website: <a
              href="https://www.netlinks.net"
              class="text-primary hover:underline">
              www.netlinks.net
            </a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
